      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<h3 id=\"DragonLighting-Lighting\">Lighting</h3><p>The lighting rig is rather simple. My main focus was to shape and outline the features of the dragon nicely. I opted for a slightly stronger rim light that accentuates the teeth and head plates to give it a more cinematic look. The key light is placed at a slight angle from the front with a directional fall of light to create hard shadows. I then used an HDRI for fill light, which helps avoid completely black areas.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"lights-breakdown.gif\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/656834669/lights-breakdown.gif?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762591731675&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=912\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/656834669/lights-breakdown.gif?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762591731675&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"1800\" data-width=\"1500\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"657228043\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"lights-breakdown.gif\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/gif\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"656834669\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"f6796130-05a5-4e17-ad56-ecae2fd4aa1e\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/656834669/lights-breakdown.gif?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762591731675&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1500&amp;height=1800 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/656834669/lights-breakdown.gif?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1762591731675&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=912 1x\"></span><p /><div class=\"panel conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"\" data-macro-name=\"panel\" style=\"background-color: #EAE6FF;border-color: #998DD9;border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"panelContent\" style=\"background-color: #EAE6FF;\">\n<p>Tip 1: For a nicely balanced starting point, use a mid-gray material with a roughness of 0.65.</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"panel conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"\" data-macro-name=\"panel\" style=\"background-color: #EAE6FF;border-color: #998DD9;border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"panelContent\" style=\"background-color: #EAE6FF;\">\n<p>Tip 2: Analyzing real-life studio photography can give you a good idea of light placement and settings.</p>\n</div></div><p /><hr/>"
    }
